_**This post is part of our special coverage of[Bahrain Protests
2011](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/bahrain-
protests-2011/).**_

Reports of shootings in different locations in the Bahraini capital of Manama,
flooded social media websites in the afternoon of this Friday 18 February,
2011. The video below posted by Youtube user
[habib2day](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hRVSmigzpos) appears to show
injured protestors in the aftermath of the attack.

Reactions from Twitter have been quick to emerge:

> @[angryarabiya](http://www.twitter.com/angryarabiya) As the sun sets, many
> thousands are being attacked by riot police, and police shooting from
> buildings rooftops! #bahrain #bahrein #feb14

> @[leildehati](http://www.twitter.com/leildehati) my cousin is very close to
> salmaniya. she is hearing shootings!!!!!! #bahrain

> @[emile_hokayem](http://www.twitter.com/emile_hokayem) Just ran into group
> of protesters going to site of clashes. They say army firing live rounds in
> the air.

> @[rym86](http://www.twitter.com/rym86) Gunshots outside #Smc .. This is a
> humanitarian protest.. #Bahrain #feb14

> @[SuadAK](http://www.twitter.com/SuadAK) Stop the bloodshed #Bahrain

